Worker: Hmm, you're not cut out for this.

What are you saying, you rude person, making assumptions on
your own.
Worker: Ah, my bad, my bad.

Worker: You see, the tunnel ahead has this strangely hard
bedrock despite the loose ground. It's not a job just anyone
can do, so we're only letting through guys with a good
build.
I see, that's the situation.

If you're in trouble, just say so. Leave it to me. I'm
somewhat confident in my strength.

Worker: Well... I can see you've got a fine body in parts,
but...

Worker: No way I can let a girl or a kid through. There are
plenty of other places short on hands. If you don't want to
get hurt, try somewhere else.
Fuuuuuuu...
Hmph!!

How about that? If you still have doubts about my strength,
shall I try elsewhere?

Worker: You idiot! If you want to test your strength, there
are other ways! Are you trying to break the tunnel and bury
us all alive?!
Ah!? Ah, ahhhh...

I can't believe I did that... I let being underestimated get
to my head... I lost my cool...
So it seems, even though I was holding back...

Worker: You're kidding me... Are you from the Orc tribe or
something?

It looks like there's another rock worth smashing in front
of me...

Worker: Anyway! I get it now, your strength is incredible!
Young and beautiful with grace, and despite being young and
beautiful, you're quite something...!!!
That's right, that's right. Mhm mhm.

Worker: In fact, I'm the one asking you! We're really
struggling here! It might be tough work, but could you lend
us your strength?
Leave it to me, this is also a knight's duty.

Worker: Knight...? What do you mean? Well, never mind. The
workers inside will explain the details. Hurry up and get
inside and break that bedrock! I'm counting on you!

Worker: The monsters around here are small fry by nature,
but there's a strangely large number of big ones. Well,
they're still timid, so they ain't dangerous unless you
provoke them, but it's still startling when you run into
'em.

Worker: I used to be soaked in the life of a mercenary, just
swinging a stick and bashing people's heads in, and now here
I am, swinging a stick at a wall. Life's strange, ain't it?

Worker: I saw someone's head and arms get blown off when
they hit a gas pocket the other day.

Worker: It's ironic, isn't it? Normally, it's so dim that I
don't even care about the faces of the guys working next to
me, but in moments like that, everything is seen so clearly.
Excuse me, I'd like to ask where the materials depot is.
Worker: Huh? What's up, are you new here?

Yes, that's right. I'm still not familiar with how things
work around here.

(Just arrived, huh. Come to think of it, I don't know
exactly either... How long was it before I regained
consciousness after being brought here...)
Worker: Heh, is that so. Heh...

Hey, hey. Don't stare at me like that. I'm not exactly
dressed to impress...!
Worker: ... You interested in the secrets of this place?
Secrets? What brought this on all of a sudden?

Worker: Yeah. Like what kind of place this is and what we're
being made to dig for, you know? Don't you wanna know?

(Hmm. I just tried striking up a conversation without much
thought and got an unexpected response. Even though we're
far from the royal capital, I certainly didn't know about a
place like this.)

(I can guess what this guy's angle is... But it's true,
having even a little information could be beneficial
considering what lies ahead.)

That would be appreciated, indeed. I've been brought here
not too long ago myself. I'd be grateful if you could share
what you know.

Worker: Hey now, you think I'm gonna tell you for free?
Don't joke with me, it's troubling.

Worker: Not that I was sizing you up by looking at your body
or anything...

Worker: Heh heh heh, living in these tunnels for so long has
got me 'pent-up', if you know what I mean. If you want me to
tell you, you get what I'm asking for, right...?
Tch... As I thought...! You...!
What do you want me to do? I'd appreciate it if you could tell me.
You scoundrel...! Fine, do as you please with my body...!
What a fool! Scum! I'll straighten out your twisted nature!!

Worker: Ouch ouch ouch... There's no need to hit me all of a
sudden... It was just a joke, a joke.

In this pit of the earth, while there's understanding of
each other's circumstances, yet no one comes together or
lends a hand!

And if someone finds another in a weaker position, then they
try to exploit them and take advantage for themselves!

While the place you were hit still hurts, maybe you'll
reflect on your actions and thoughts a bit! That's what you
deserve!
Worker: Grr... Spouting all that righteous stuff...!

What do you mean 'pent-up'? Filth! Do you see women as
nothing more than objects of lust, seriously! Think before
you speak!

That sort of thing should be, well... I'm not very
knowledgeable about it, but maybe after getting to know each
other better, and then going through the proper steps? And
then when things feel right, maybe then it would be okay to
ask...?

Worker: (Eh? What's with this sudden show of duality...? Is
this the blooming of a maiden's heart deep underground...??)

What are you on about! Did I say something so strange!? You
provoke me and then go silent...!
Worker: ... Could this feeling be... love?
I can't deal with this. I'm leaving.

Worker: Sorry sorry! It was just a joke! Right, about the
secrets of this place?
First comes an apology and some reflection.

Worker: My bad! My bad! You looked like a newbie so I just
wanted to tease you a bit! Whatever your response was going
to be, I was planning to reveal it was all just a joke once
I saw your troubled face!

"Starting off with a high price" might be the way things are
done here, but you should polish your eye for appraisal a
bit more. Now let's hear it, the information about this
place that you claim to know.

Worker: Though I gotta say, it's not really anything
significant.

Worker: Sure, now I might be stuck digging holes in a place
like this for reasons, but before coming here I was involved
in magical research. Quite involved indeed.
Oh? That's quite something. Please continue?

Worker: That's why I know, see. This mine is unusual because
there are high concentrations of magical power flowing
through it everywhere, like veins.

Worker: Whether we're inside a mountain or underground, I
can't say, but it runs all over the place. It must be a
characteristic of the land itself. It's quite mysterious.

Worker: And after working here for a while, I've realized
that when we dig near these veins of magical power, we seem
to find the stones they're after.

Worker: It's not gold or gems or anything like that; we're
made to dig up these stones. To the untrained eye of an
amateur, they probably just look like pretty unusual stones.

I thought mining was about following veins of stone to
extract ore, but here we're reading veins of magical power
to dig up stones. That's unheard of.

Should we call the stones that are mined "magical crystals"?
What kind of properties do they have? What exactly are we
being made to dig up?

Worker: Who knows? Maybe it would be clear if examined in a
proper facility. In the end, I don't know the details.

Worker: Nor do I know what they're used for or who's buying
them. As for the latter, it's better not to know if you want
to get out of here alive.
(Hmm, I see... I should keep this in mind.)
That was an interesting story. I appreciate it.

Worker: Don't mention it, don't mention it. Around here,
there aren't many who'd indulge in this type of conversation
that doesn't fill one's belly.

Worker: Talking with people is indeed enjoyable. It was only
for a short while, but it distracted me from the depressing
work.
Is that so? Well, that's good to hear.
Worker: Yeah! You too, sis, hang in there!

Worker: Hey, sis. What's up? If you slack off, the guards
will give us hell, you know?
I want to hear about the features of the mine again.
Yeah, you work hard too.

Worker: I may be like this now, but before I ended up here,
I was involved in magical research for work.

Worker: That's why I understand, this mine is unusual
because there are streams of high-density magical power
running through it like veins.

Worker: I don't know if we're inside a mountain or
underground, but it's running all over the place. It must be
a characteristic of the land itself, but it's strange.

Worker: And after working here for a while, I've realized
that if you dig near these veins of magical power, you seem
to find the stones we're after. That's the job we've been
forced to do, digging them out.

Worker: That's about all I know. In the end, I have no idea
what they're used for or who's buying them.
Worker: Yeah, sure.
Worker: The quotas are so tough...

Worker: "You seem to have plenty of energy left, that's
good. The one who just came in..."

Worker: "It feels like someone is always watching... It's so
unpleasant to feel like your work is constantly being
judged..."

Worker: That girl has been looking this way for a while now,
maybe I should talk to her sometimes?

Worker: If the work goes well, there'll be a little reward
for you! I'm counting on you!

Worker: Thanks a lot, sis! If you ever run into trouble,
just say the word! Next time, I'll be the one to lend you a
hand!
